endencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Consider the variable `$lastException` of type `\\Exception|null`..\r\nI'm sure that the variable at a certain point can only contain an `\\Exception`, so I want to use annotation:\r\n\r\n``/** @var \\Exception $lastException */``\r\n``throw $lastException;``\r\n\r\nThis appears to be doing nothing at all (tested on versions 1.1.9 & 3.4.7):\r\n> ERROR: InvalidThrow - modules/saml/lib/Message.php:419:9 - Cannot throw null as it does not extend Exception or implement Throwable\r\n>         /** @var \\Exception $lastException */\r\n>         throw $lastException;\r\n\r\nThe only way around this I could think of was to either use `/** @psalm-suppress InvalidThrow */` to suppress the false-positive or to insert another assignment like this:\r\n\r\n``/** @var \\Exception $lastException */``\r\n``$lastException = $lastException;``\r\n``throw $lastException;``\r\n\r\nBoth do the trick, but neither is really a solution if you ask me..","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com